# W3: an element literal inside a nested @{ } hole of a js`` literal seated in a
# {{ }} Go block (`{{ h := js`f(@{ <b>y</b> })` }}`). Like the top-level form,
# the hole must reassemble to a string seed, but an element value is a gsx.Node
# closure — a single positioned "unsupported-node" diagnostic. The fix keeps the
# GoBlock probe skeleton VALID (holeProbeSeed lowers the element part to a
# nil-returning _gsxrt.Node placeholder) so emit's assembleHoleSeed rejection is
# the one message, not a parser cascade from raw `<b>y</b>` in the skeleton.
# Contrast a `<tag>` written DIRECTLY in a {{ }} block (element_rejected.txtar),
# which analyze diagnoses itself via goBlockElementPart.
-- input.gsx --
package demo

component Page() {
	{{ h := js`f(@{ <b>y</b> })` }}
	<button @click={h}>x</button>
}
-- invoke --
Page()
-- diagnostics.golden --
4:16: element literals are not supported inside this interpolation position; bind the element to a variable in a {{ }} block or use a { } child position
-- render.golden --
